# Edge Functions and Middleware

Vercel Edge Functions and Middleware execute on V8 isolates at CDN nodes worldwide. They start in under 1ms (no cold start penalty) and process requests close to the end user. The edge runtime uses Web standard APIs (fetch, Request, Response, crypto) rather than Node.js APIs.

## Edge Middleware

Middleware runs before every matched request. Define it in `middleware.ts` (or `.js`) at the project root:

```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import type { NextRequest } from "next/server";

export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  // Geolocation-based routing
  const country = request.geo?.country || "US";
  if (country === "DE") {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL("/de", request.url));
  }

  // Add custom headers
  const response = NextResponse.next();
  response.headers.set("x-country", country);
  return response;
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ["/api/:path*", "/dashboard/:path*"],
};
```

## Edge Functions

Standalone edge functions use the `edge` runtime:

```typescript
// app/api/fast/route.ts
export const runtime = "edge";

export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const data = await fetch("https://api.example.com/data");
  return new Response(JSON.stringify(await data.json()), {
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
  });
}
```

### Standalone (api/ directory)

```javascript
// api/location.js
export const config = { runtime: "edge" };

export default async function handler(req) {
  return new Response(
    JSON.stringify({
      city: req.geo?.city,
      country: req.geo?.country,
      region: req.geo?.region,
    }),
    { headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" } }
  );
}
```

## Matchers

Control which paths middleware applies to:

```typescript
export const config = {
  matcher: [
    "/api/:path*",           // all API routes
    "/dashboard/:path*",     // dashboard pages
    "/((?!_next|favicon.ico).*)",  // all except static assets
  ],
};
```

## Geolocation

The `request.geo` object provides:

| Property | Type | Example |
|----------|------|----------|
| `city` | string | `"San Francisco"` |
| `country` | string | `"US"` |
| `region` | string | `"CA"` |
| `latitude` | string | `"37.7749"` |
| `longitude` | string | `"-122.4194"` |

## Edge vs Serverless

| Feature | Edge | Serverless |
|---------|------|------------|
| Cold start | <1ms | 100ms-2s |
| Runtime | V8 isolates (Web APIs) | Full Node.js / Python / Go |
| Max duration | 30s | 10s-900s |
| Node.js APIs | Limited (no fs, net) | Full support |
| Global distribution | All CDN nodes | Single region |
| Best for | Auth, routing, geolocation | DB queries, heavy compute |
